{{wikipedia|dab=backlash (disambiguation)|backlash}}

===Etymology===
From {{compound|en|back|lash}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈbækˌlæʃ/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-backlash.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|æʃ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es}}

# A sudden backward motion.
# A negative [[reaction]], [[objection]] or [[outcry]], especially of a [[violent]] or [[abrupt]] nature.
#: ''The public '''backlash''' to the proposal was quick and insistent.''
# {{lb|en|mechanics}} The [[distance]] through which one part of connected machinery, as a [[wheel]], [[piston]], or [[screw]], can be moved without moving the connected parts, resulting from [[loose]]ness in fitting or from wear.
# The [[jarring]] or [[reflex]] motion caused in badly fitting machinery by irregularities in velocity or a reverse of motion.

